ut, she put out the tourch and placed it down, a small noise cam efrom it and she heard one of the guards grunt. She tensed up and grabbed her bow and arrow, peaking over the large boulder she hid behind, she saw only two guards...lucky for her, it would be easier fighting one then two. She strung her bow and let an arrow fly, right into the neck of one of the guards. The other one grabbed his sword as his partner fell to the floor in a large lump on the floor. She screamed and ran out behind the boulder, sword gripped tightly in her hand, the uard saw her and growled, swiping his old sword towards her, she jumped out of the way and blocked his blade, tripping over a rock, she fell to the ground, the edge of his blade hit her and slashed her leg. Blood began to run down he rleg as she hopped to her feet and swung her sword, catching him right in the stomach, she lifted the blade up, cutting through his chest, abdomen, right up to his throat. Another guard ran out from the dark, his elbow crashing into her lip, splitting it as his dagger rammed into her arm, she screamed and spun, kicking him in the groin and bringing the hilt of her sword down on his neck, she then twisted his head and broke his neck, cursing, she threw his body to the ground. Holding her stance once more she looked around, everything seemed quiet. She plopped down on the floor and grabbed her bag, she took a piece of swaddling from it, she lay her head against a rock and began to breath deeply. Her arm was going numb. She couldnt have this, not now.~<br>
&quot;Hera give me strength.&quot; ~ She wispered to the empty chamber, as she spoke those words, she felt as if someone was embracing her, and she smiled, she knew Hera had heard her. Gritting her teeth together, she gripped the hilt of the dagger and yanked it quickly out, screaming loudly. Taking a deep breath, she wrapped the swadling around the wound as it bleed profusly. Then got ot her feet. She walked to the wall and moved a branch that extended from it. The door quickly opened and she walked into the chamber, it was a small room, tourches alligned the wall casting off an erie glow. In the center, stood a column, on it, the dagger stood. The light relecting off of it making it look almost mystical. She walked over and looked at it, biting her bottom lip, she grabbed the hilt and held it up, a smile of triumph on her face. She placed it into her sachel and ran as fast as she could out of the room, almost getting caught between the massive rock doors as they closed. She followed her path and was outside quickly, into the now bright sunfilled mountain cliffs.~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonvelaska.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Velaska</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/19/02 6:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/amaz0nbich/images/velaskabich.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arriving in Crete</span><hr size=1> ~ As she walked from the caves, she shielded her eyes from the sun until her eyes adjusted to the sunlight. She blinked a few times then opened 