ck in and made a fire to lay by, she unrolled her bedding and was fast to sleep. In the morning she would set off to find the underground hall she so long ago heard of.~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonvelaska.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Velaska</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(1/25/02 1:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=228.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Morning Comes</span><hr size=1> ~ Velaska had slept well past thetime she wanted to, the sun was allready high in the sky. But it just proved that she must of been tired. Her body needed the rest after the fight the day earlier. She looked to her wound and flinched as she saw it red and probably infected. She didn't worry about it, Velaska was one who hardly worried about such trivial things, besides, before the sunset, there was a good chance it would be completly healed. She got up, ate some of the food she brought along with her and went outside. Nightmare was glad to see her up, and she gave the mare some water and food, waited till she was done then mounted her. Off into the thick of the woods again, but she felt more safe this time, she was in amazon territory. She looked around for any signs of amazon life, but sadly, didnt find any. It was apparent this tribe was gone. Velaska hopped thay they just relocated. On and on she went , until she reached the bottom of the cave she was looking for. Dismounting, she wispered to Nightmare to go on back to Themiscrya, she would meet her back there, she then swat the mare on her side and Nightmare rode off. Velaska stood there, watching her leave. She then turned on her heel and walked into the cave. Once inside, a boulder slid in place to block the way back out. A tight knot formed in the Queen's gut as two female forms appeared before her. They wore the cloths of peasents, but Velaska knew of them, they were the Guardians of the Ambrosia. Ancient Amazons who guard the sacred caves.~<br>
